<h1 id="wi-fi" class="step">Test your Wi-Fi</h1>

Problems with Wi-Fi are unfortunately quite common in Tails and Linux in
general. To test if your Wi-Fi interface works in Tails:

1. Open the system menu in the top-right corner:

   [[!img doc/first_steps/desktop/system-with-wifi-only.png link="no" class="screenshot" alt=""]]

1. Click [[!img lib/go-next.png link="no" class="symbolic" alt=""]] on the
   right of the **Wi-Fi** button.

   A list of available Wi-Fi networks appears below the **Wi-Fi** button.

1. After establishing a connection to a local network, the *Tor Connection*
   assistant appears to help you connect to the Tor
   network.

   [[!img doc/anonymous_internet/tor/tor-connection.png link="no" class="screenshot" alt=""]]

   <div class="next">

   <p>To learn more about the Tor network, go to [[Connecting to the Tor
   network|doc/anonymous_internet/tor]].</p>

   </div>

